==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Santonin
<hw>San"to*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>herba
santonica</ets>, a kind of plant, fr. <ets>Santoni</ets> a people of
Aquitania; cf. Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>santonine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline substance having a bitter
taste, extracted from the buds of levant wormseed and used as an
anthelmintic. It occassions a peculiar temporary color blindness,
causing objects to appear as if seen through a yellow glass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Santoninate</ent>⟦br⟧
